Testimony alert 🚨 
Growing up I’ve always been a smart kid , lack of motivation and confidence is something I’ve been working on over the years when it came to applying myself. Always been in honors over the years from elementary (top class) high school, college (deans list) to now having straight A’s. 

I remember the end of 12th grade, I didn’t have confidence in thinking I could ever make it into college because I wasn’t a good test taker (anxiety ; sitting in class doing the test thinking about life - what would happen if I didn’t pass? What would I do next? Etc) instead of just focusing on the test (the moment) To ended up in remedial , scoring the highest in the class (then the lord reminded me ‘ uhm you wasn’t supposed to be in that class in the first place but at the same time providing Grace of preparation) 
Set backs aren’t there to define you but rather prepare you for what’s coming!!! 

The lord saying I know the plans I have for you … Jeremiah 29:11 📖 
going through all the emotions and still remaining consistent regardless of the circumstances. 

This new season of becoming I’ve learnt to Walk with the Lord as he Pace me into my divine calling one step at a time 👣 

I hope this could be of encouragement to continue on with your studies and to remain Trusting in the Lord because he was reveal the truth for your life and those around you.

Thank you Jesus 🙌🏾☺️🥹 only the Lord knows
